profile.title: DDS
profile.bio:
Sharareh Tajbakhsh DDS is a dentist who specializes in dentist. Dr. Tajbakhsh is licensed to practice in California. She practices dentist at Cupertino Dental Group in 10383 Torre Ave Ste 1, Cupertino.

Dr. Sharareh Tajbakhsh is a Prosthodontist specializing in porcelain veneers, full mouth rehabilitation, and the planning and placement of implant restorations.

Dr. Tajbakhsh received her Doctor of Dental Surgery from the University of Pacific, Arthur A. Dugoni School of Dentistry in San Francisco. Upon graduation she practiced general dentistry in Daly City, and continued on at the University of the Pacific, where she was an instructor for over seven years. Desiring to further her education, she attended the University of Washingtonâ€™s nationally accredited prosthodontics program in Seattle, where she obtained her Certificate in Prosthodontics, and a Masters of Science in Dentistry. In 2009 she was awarded the David H. Wands fellowship, which aims to encourage recipients to give back to dental education.

Dr. Tajbakhsh's practice philosophy is to always strive for perfection. She is only satisfied when she achieves excellence and believes it is essential to really listen to the patients and understand their needs and desires. Her multiple language skills in English, French, Spanish, and Farsi facilitate her day to day patient communication. She works to educate all her patients so that they can take an active roll in their treatment and accomplish the smile they desire.

Appreciating the value of the community, Dr. Tajbakhsh is committed to volunteer her services, providing dental care for patients at the Samaritan House Free Clinic, a non-profit organization located in San Mateo and Redwood City.

Dr. Sharareh Tajbakhsh is member of the American College of Prosthodontics, the American Dental Association, California Dental Association, the American Academy of Cosmetic Dentistry, the Santa Clara County Dental Society, and University of the Pacific Alumni Association, University of Washington Graduate Prosthodontic Alumni Association, Pierre Fauchard Academy, and Health Volunteer Organization.

In her free time she enjoys laughing, reading, jewelry making, and cooking. Her outdoor activities include hiking, and skiing.

Dr. Diaz-Arrastia is an associate professor in the department of Obstetrics and Gynecology at Baylor College of Medicine (BCM) and director of Gynecologic Oncology at BCM. 

Dr. Arrastia was the first to report that hysterectomies could be performed using the DaVinci (robotic) system in 2002. Likewise, she was the first physician in Texas to perform fertility-preserving radical vaginal trachelectomy surgery for invasive cervical carcinoma.

She has also served as Principal Investigator for several NIH-funded translational research projects in HPV-associated cervical neoplasia with the goal of developing robust prognostic and diagnostic biomarkers for refining the pathological staging of cervical carcinoma.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
I went to Castilleja School in Palo Alto for junior high and high school. Afterward, I went on to U.C. Davis for my undergraduate degree in Genetics. I went to medical school at Loyola Stritch School of medicine just outside of Chicago, IL. I enjoyed Chicago and living life outside of the bubble of the Bay Area for a while but was also thrilled to come back to California for my pediatric residency at Childrenâ€™s Hospital and Research Center Oakland. I am a board certified pediatrician.  I began practicing at Kaiser Permanente Redwood City in December 2005 and moved to the Kaiser Permanente satellite office in San Mateo when it opened in August 2011.

I chose to work at Kaiser because I believe it provides excellent, comprehensive medical care that is easy for patients to access. The resources that Kaiser provides, such as classes and the vast amount of web-based educational material, can be very helpful to patients.  The Kaiser Permanente system also allows me to communicate quickly and easily with my colleagues in subspecialty areas whenever the need arises.

I chose pediatrics as my specialty because the process of growing up is fascinating. I also enjoy connecting with families and believe that a partnership with the family is the core of pediatric care. All children have a network of support including school, friends, family, etc. I try to work within that network, whether it is helping make sure a child is in the right learning environment in school or offering treatment options to maximize a childâ€™s participation in his or her favorite activities. I look forward to working with you to keep your child healthy and happy.

This web site provides more detailed information on our group, location, specialties and surgeons as well as resource information concerning various orthopedic conditions.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
Dr. Hershey is a board certified orthopedic surgeon who is fellowship trained in lower extremity reconstruction at the Scripps Clinic in La Jolla California. Dr Hershey utilizes a variety of innovative surgical techniques in total knee and total hip replacement surgery to reduce discomfort and shorten the recovery time after surgery. Many options are available, including minimally invasive techniques and computer navigated knee replacements, which are tailored to meet the patient's specific needs and goals.

 

Dr. Hershey received his undergraduate degree in Pharmacy with high honors from Oregon State University. He graduated from medical school cum laude at Oregon Health Sciences University where he also completed his orthopedic surgical residency. Dr Hershey's academic excellence was recognized by admittance to the Rho Chi pharmacy honor society and the Alpha Omega Alpha medical honor society. He went on to complete his fellowship in lower extremity reconstruction at the Scripps Clinic and Research Foundation before moving back to Salinas in 1995.

Dr Hershey is currently the Chief of Surgery at Salinas Valley Memorial Hospital where he previously served as the Head of Surgical Quality Improvement. He is a fellow of the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons, and is a member of the Monterey County Medical Society and the California Orthopedic Association.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
I was born and raised in Manila, Philippines and immigrated to the United States at age 15. Growing up in a third world country sensitized me to the special care children need. At the age of 8, I declared to my parents I was going to be a pediatrician and haven't looked back since.

I obtained my medical degree from the University of California, Los Angeles. I then completed my pediatric residency at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center in Southern California. During my residency training, I received an excellence award for the care of pediatric patients and my close collaboration with the nursing staff. I was also the residency program representative to the American Academy of Pediatrics. I also completed a month of training in infectious disease at the Philippine General Hospital. 
  
I started working at Kaiser Permanente in July 1997. Since then I have served as one of the Assistant Chiefs of Pediatrics and currently serve as Chief of Pediatrics at the San Jose facility. Working at Kaiser Permanente has allowed me to pursue my clinical interests in preventing obesity and neonatal sepsis and managing asthma.  I am a fellow of the American Academy of Pediatrics and a member of the Santa Clara County Medical Association. I am board certified with the American Board of Pediatrics in the specialty of pediatrics.
